                    <msContents>
                        <summary><title xml:lang="da">Brevbog for Dueholm Kloster: Dueholms
                                Diplomatarium II</title>
                            <title xml:lang="en">Cartulary from Dueholm</title></summary>
                        <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                    </msContents>
                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc form="codex">
                            <supportDesc material="chart">
                                <support>
                                    <p>
                                        <material>Paper.</material>
                                    </p>
                                </support>
                                <extent>48, fols 17-20, 27, 29v-36 are blank; fols 4r, 7v, 9r, 11v,
                                    12, and 23v only have rubrics. <dimensions type="leaf"
                                        scope="all">
                                        <height unit="mm">210</height>
                                        <width unit="mm">150</width>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </extent>
                                <condition>
                                    <p>The bottom of fols 37, 45 and 46 are damaged; there are
                                        several lacunae.</p>
                                </condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <additions>
                            <p>On the originally blank f. 48v a sixteenth century hand wrote: <q
                                    xml:lang="da">Abell Andersdatter</q>. There is also a and <q
                                    xml:lang="da">Erlig og wellbwrdige fru Ellen S. Thygge
                                    Sandbergs</q>. The same page also contains a religious apothegm
                                in Latin, most probably in Abel Andersdatter's hand: <q
                                    xml:lang="la">Dominus vobiscum, oremus protector noster
                                    indesperantium deus ut te rectore te duce te thranciamus per
                                    omnia secula seculorum. Amen</q>. At f. 17r Árni Magnússon
                                wrote: <q xml:lang="la">Multa desunt</q>.</p>
                        </additions>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin when="1527" cert="high" evidence="internal">
                            <p>Written in Dueholm, Northern Jutland in
                                    <origPlace>Denmark</origPlace>
                                <origDate when="1527">1527</origDate>; the date is found on ff. 39r
                                and 47v.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>The manuscript belonged to <name type="person" key="AbeGun001">Abel
                                    Andersdatter</name> who wrote her name at f. 48v. The name of
                                Thyge Sandberg's widow, Ellen Krastrup is also found at the same
                                page.</p>
                        </provenance>
                    </history>
